            <h2 style="margin-top: 80px">What does the name Klloom mean?</h2>
            <p>The name Klloom comes from “darK smaLL rOOM”, which is related to the origin of photography, when the so-called pinhole cameras were made with a closed chamber (camera obscura) containing a small hole without lens. The use of the small and dark room was also present in the process of developing films, when it was necessary to isolate them in a lightproof space.</p>
            <p>Like Klloom's name, our logo was also inspired by photography, and more directly by the optical process that happens at the light input of a pinhole camera.</p>

            <h2>Can I license my photos on Klloom without donating?</h2>
            <p>Fortunately not. :) Donation is an essential part of this community. We do believe in new ways of generating and sharing wealth.</p>

            <h2>Why all the donation is sent to the Red Cross only?</h2>
            <p>Klloom is the world's first tangible initiative that carries a social compromise as an intrinsic part of its core business, and choosing trustworthy Humanitarian Cause organizations is essential for us to guarantee the reliability of our model.</p>
