            <p>If you are from a Global Humanitarian Organization and want to be part of our donation chain, please send an email to <a href="mailto:donation@klloom.com" title="donation@klloom.com">donation@klloom.com</a>.</p>

            <h2>Is Klloom an NGO (Non-governmental Organization)?</h2>
            <p>No, it isn't. We just want to be an example of honest and sincere business that, besides being a business, also provide a new income alternative for photo lovers and generate a powerful social contribution mechanism.</p>

            <h2>Is Klloom a Red Cross initiative?</h2>
            <p>No, it isn't. Klloom is a private, commercial company with an intrinsic social goal. We are not commercially associated (by law) to any Organization or Institute, even though our business backbone includes connecting to Global Humanitarian Organizations to which we donate part of our incomes. Red Cross is our first donation partner, which means that 20% of our gross licensing incomes are donated to them.</p>

            <h2>Can I sell my photos on Klloom and on other websites at the same time?</h2>
            <p>Yes, you can sell your image through other commercial licensing vendors, or directly to commercial buyers. But your image must not be available on any free stock image bank (such as Pexels or Unsplash). Besides, since Klloom’s photos have an intrinsic social purpose involved, we would be very grateful if you chose photos from your collection exclusively for licensing on Klloom.</p>

            <h2>Why is PayPal the only payment method offered?</h2>
            <p>For your security and privacy, Klloom won't keep any credit card information of its users, as well as their address information. If you are buying a photo, you will be redirected to a secure payment environment outside of Klloom after the checkout, where you will be asked to enter your PayPal login information. So far, PayPal is the more suitable payment platform for Klloom users to avoid sharing extra personal information with us. However, we do consider having other payment methods available in the near future, as long as they allow users to carry on with the payment process outside of Klloom.</p>

            <h2>Does Klloom also offers monthly or annual subscriptions?</h2>
            <p>Not yet. For now, we need to test our codes and business model in a simpler way. We think it may be possible in the future, though. It’s just a start.</p>

            <h2>Does Klloom curate and approve the photos before they are published?</h2>
            <p>No, we don't curate the photos beforehand. Instead, Klloom trusts and depends on its user community’s wisdom and reasonableness to identify, judge, rate and report the content that may be inappropriate, offensive or not in accordance with our Terms and our Behavior Guidelines.</p>
            <p>You can always hit our Report button to disclose any member. Behavior outside of Klloom guidelines may result in account suspension or permanent removal from our network. We have created a list of good-conduct rules that applies not only to comments and texts, but also to all uploaded images. By using Klloom, you must adhere to these guidelines.</p>

            <h2>Can I upload illustrations and graphic design content?</h2>
            <p>Currently, Klloom is not accepting illustration, painting and graphic design content for licensing on the website. We are a photography licensing platform.</p>

            <h2>How should I proceed in case of my photo being reported?</h2>
            <p>Those who had their content removed or made inaccessible in response to a notice of infringement may provide Klloom with a counter notice in writing to <a href="mailto:legal@klloom.com" title="legal@klloom.com">legal@klloom.com</a> if they feel that their content is not infringing. Please include in your counter notice enough information to enable Klloom to make a reasonable resolution. You must note that you may be held responsible for damages (including costs and attorneys' fees) for giving a false account that your content is not infringing any terms or behavior guidelines.</p>

            <h2>How many times can I download the photo after paying for its license?</h2>
            <p>You can download the photo you bought unlimited times while it's available for licensing on the website. We do recommend, though, that you download your file as soon as it appears in the My Purchased Photos in your user settings page. Please keep your own backup of the file as it may become not available for licensing in the future. The download link goes accessible soon after your payment is confirmed.</p>
            <p>Once you downloaded it, there is no expiration or end date on your rights to use the image.</p>

            <h2>Who, besides me, can use the photo after I downloaded it?</h2>
            <p>The license is granted to one person (including a company employee). Additional licenses must be obtained for each member of your organization or company who will use the image.</p>
            <p>There are two exceptions, though:</p>
            <ol type="a">
