            <h2>When should I mark my photo as “Editorial Use Only”?</h2>
            <p>Images marked "Editorial Use Only” add an exception to the Klloom Standard License.</p>
            <p>When you mark your photo as "Editorial Use Only" you are saying that it is not allowed to be used for any commercial purpose, including promotional, endorsement, advertorial, advertising or merchandising purpose.</p>
            <p>You should (probably) mark your photo as Editorial Use Only if:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>You are a celebrity, public figure or fashion model, and you appears in the photo.</li>
                <li>You haven’t been authorized by all models and/or properties owners/representatives that appears or have their property depicted in your photo with a valid Release.</li>
                <li>You don’t want your photo to be used for commercial purposes (for whatever reason).</li>
